¬ö√]<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1072";s:4:"name";s:11:"Acid Reflux";s:4:"slug";s:11:"acid-reflux";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1072";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:3631:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">Our food habits have changed a lot over a few decades and the popularity of fast food has increased astonishingly, resulting in a large number of diseases/conditions. Acid Reflux literally means stomach acid traveling up into your throat creating a heartburn feeling. If this happens often, it can lead to Gastro-oesophageal Reflux disease (GERD).</span>

<b>A few common symptoms of Acid Reflux are:</b>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Heartburn</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Regurgitation: A sour taste in your mouth due to stomach acids</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bloating</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bloody or black stools or bloody vomiting</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Burping</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hiccups that don't let up</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nausea</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Weight loss for no known reason</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dry cough, hoarseness, or chronic sore throat</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Taking the right measures in your daily lifestyle can help to treat Acid reflux. A few changes you should consider are mentioned below:</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Eat smaller meals. Avoid Oily &amp; fried foods.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Add green leafy vegetables to your diet.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Quit smoking.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Don‚Äôt lie down immediately after eating.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Don't wear tight clothes or tight belts.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you're overweight, exercise to lose weight.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Go for a walk or indulge in a fitness activity daily.</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Acid reflux is a chronic disease and can make your life difficult. It‚Äôs better to take care of yourself and improve your habits for a better life.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done path-breaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that ‚ÄúIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.‚Äù </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of Acid Reflux is just </span><b>Fear. Clutching fear</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One way of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations. Doing this regularly can help to reduce the debilitating effects of this illness.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for healing Acid reflux is</span><b><i>: </i></b><b>I breathe freely and fully. I am safe. I trust the process of life.</b>

